	<meta property="og:description" content="For someone who expends a lot of energy on her meals, I‚Äôm a tad lazy when it comes to their attendant beverages. I mean, I like a good glass of wine‚Äîor beer, or Lillet, or port, or gin‚Äîas much as the next girl, but for me, it‚Äôs kind of an afterthought. I need something to moisten the taste buds, of course, but it‚Äôs secondary to the meal itself. In some circles, this is tantamount to blasphemy, I know, but eh, well, it‚Äôs just the way I am. I could, I guess, blame it on my laughable inability to hold my liquor. (Legend has it that I once had a couple of beers and, with a slow roll of the head,&hellip;" />
